Have you ever been to a big supermarket and tried to find something you really like or want , looking throug shelves and not finding that in the end .
What do you feel ?
You have to be very disappointed .
There are a lot of situations which could make you feel similar while you do shopping .
You might spend too much money and buy something you do n't really need .
You can also buy something which later turns out to be out of order .
So you have to complain about it .
Very often if a shop assistant is not always helpful so you lose your money and your time .
Moreover , you can face the an agressive and maybe even drunk shop assistant or manager .
This leads to an escalation of your anger .
Sometimes you can find a bargain .
You are very happy to buy a dress or a suit for a good price .
But at home you noticed that there was a tear on your sleeve .
And you ca n't of course to give it back because the price was lowered and your dress is not under guarantee .
You can also face an unpleasant situation connected with money .
Somebody could give do n't enough change .
How would you feel ? Deceived ?
So if you do n't want to feel deceived or offended , think twice before you decide to go shopping .
It a very depressing point of view , is n't it ? )
